# Ticket 5 - DMZ Server Access Issue

## Scenario

Users outside the DMZ were unable to access DMZ-Server1.

## Investigation

### Tools Used

* Linux Networking Commands
* Netplan
* Firewall Analysis

### Commands

```bash
ip addr
ip route
cat /etc/netplan/01-netcfg.yaml
```

### Findings

DMZ-Server1 contained incorrect network settings and firewall rules were preventing access.

Incorrect Configuration:

```text
IP Address: 10.10.90.10
Gateway: 10.10.90.1
```

Correct Configuration:

```text
IP Address: 10.10.20.10
Gateway: 10.10.20.254
```

## Root Cause

Improper firewall configuration and incorrect server network settings prevented access to the DMZ host.

## Resolution

Corrected firewall rules, updated server network settings, and verified connectivity.

## Skills Demonstrated

* Firewall Troubleshooting
* Linux Administration
* DMZ Architecture
* Network Configuration

